Description: Fragment of Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Oval handle at neck join. Perhaps a fractional jar. Rectangular stamp. Clay near fine light pink-brown; cream slip.
Curator's comments: Drawn by Petrie (Petrie diary, 1884-1885 (EES Archive XVII 47), p..181, 27). Name Komos.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0979)
